 ABISOYE JOHNSON FORMER Senate President Bukola Saraki, on Tuesday, led a delegation of the Peoples Democratic Party leaders to visit former President Olusegun Obasanjo at his Pent House, Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library residence, in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. It was not clear whether the visit of the PDP stakeholders was in furtherance of the activities of the party’s National Reconciliation and Strategy Committee, headed by Saraki. The former President has made it clear on several occasions that he is not a member of any political party. However, the closed-door meeting held during the visit might not be unconnected with seeking his advice on how to proceed in the efforts at returning PDP back to power come 2023. In the delegation were Former Governor of Osun State, Olagunsoye Oyinlola, former Governor of Katsina State, brahim Shehu Shema; former Governor of Gombe State, Ibrahim Hassan Dankwambo; and former Governor of Cross River State, Liyel Imoke, among others. However, THE POINT learnt that the PDP had put structures in place to bring all aggrieved members together across the zones, including the South West, in preparation for the 2023 polls. “The meeting with Baba was to brainstorm with him and seek his wise counsel. Baba remains the father of Nigeria’s politics,” a source close to the visit, said. 